ly proven management companies participate in the Golden Visa program, and startups cannot participate.\r\n\r\nThe minimum investment amount here is 500,000€, the deposit can be returned after 5 years if you apply for citizenship, but it must be left in the fund to continue to maintain residency status'),(1626,115,'_description7','field_67740eddb4e73'),(1627,115,'image7','114'),(1628,115,'_image7','field_67740ee5b4e74'),(1629,115,'title8','Visa'),(1630,115,'_title8','field_677412a0e56c1'),(1631,115,'subtitle8','type of visa'),(1632,115,'_subtitle8','field_677412a4e56c2'),(1633,115,'type_of_visa_0_title','Portugal Retirement Visa or Passive Income Visa'),(1634,115,'_type_of_visa_0_title','field_677429c2ad418'),(1635,115,'type_of_visa_0_subtitle','D7 Visa -'),(1636,115,'_type_of_visa_0_subtitle','field_677429c8ad419'),(1637,115,'type_of_visa_0_description','The Portuguese government introduced a special type of visa in 2007: the D7 visa.  It is also known as the Retirement Visa or Passive Income Visa.\r\n\r\nThis residence visa allows any non-EU/EEA/Swiss citizen who has a reasonable regular net passive income to apply for residence in Portugal. This income can come from pensions, transferable equity, real estate, intellectual property, or financial investment.\r\n\r\nThe minimum amount required to be eligible for this visa is an annual income of 8,460 euros, plus 50% of this amount for the spouse and 30% for each dependent child. This is regardless of the person\'s country of origin.\r\n\r\nThis visa allows you and your family to reside legally in Portugal. It is designed to attract retired people and those living on passive income to reside in Portugal, in an effort to boost the economy. In addition, holders of this visa are not prevented from working in Portugal.'),(1638,115,'_type_of_visa_0_description','field_677429d3ad41a'),(1639,115,'type_of_visa_1_title','Entrepreneur vis'),(1640,115,'_type_of_visa_1_title','field_677429c2ad418'),(1641,115,'type_of_visa_1_subt